GIT Class -4


TOPIC: GIT CHERRY-PICK, GIT RESTORE, GIT STASH & GITHUB INTRODUCTION


GIT COMMANDS
=============

* yum install git                        ---------------------> command to install git
* git init                               ---------------------> command to initialize git
* git checkout -b newbranchname          ---------------------> command to create a new branch and switch to that created new branch as well
* git cherry-pick commit-id              ---------------------> command to get the particular commit-id from one branch to another branch
* git restore filename                   ---------------------> command to get deleted file
GIT STASH
===========
By using GIT stash command, developers can temporarily save changes made in the working directory. It allows them to quickly switch contexts when they are not quite 
ready to commit changes.And it allows them to more easily switch between branches.

Generally, the stash meaning is "store something safely in a hidden place"

* git stash       -----------------------> command to delete the changes permanently
* git stash save "message"     ----------------> command to save the stash along with the message
* git stash apply              ----------------> command to back the data again
* git stash list               ----------------> command to get the lists of stashes
* git stash clear              ----------------> command to clear all the stashes
* git stash pop                ----------------> command to delete the first stash
* git stash drop               ----------------> command to delete the latest stash
* git stash drop stash@{2}     ----------------> command to delete a particular stash


GITHUB INTRODUCTION
========================

Github is a web-based platform used for version control.
It simplifies the process of working with other people and makes it easy to collaborate on projects.
Team members can work on files and easily merge their changes in with the master branch of the project.

GITHUB COMMANDS
==================

* git remote add origin repo-url                 --------------------> command to link local-repo to central-repo
* git remote -v                                  --------------------> command to get the linked repo in github
* git push -u origin branch-name                 --------------------> command to push the code from local to central
* git push -u origin branch1 branch2             --------------------> command to used to push the code to multiple branches
* git push -u origin --all                       --------------------> command to used to push the code to all branches at a time
* git clone repo-url                             --------------------> command to used to get the code from central to local
* git pull origin branch                           --------------------> command to used to get the changes from central to local

real-time commands

* git clone github-url                 -----------------> command to get the code from github to git in ec2-instance
* git push origin branchname           -----------------> command to push the code from git ec2-instance to github (local to central)
after giving above command it will credentials of github
userame:
password: here password means need to generate the token in github
* git push -u origin branch-name      ------------------> command to push the code from git ec2-instance to github (local to central)
after giving above command it will credentials of github
